8.10	Busseto	Busseto	Busseto is a comune in the province of Parma, in Emilia-Romagna in Northern Italy. It was the capital of Stato Pallavicino. Opera composer Giuseppe Verdi was born in the nearby village of Le Roncole and he moved there in 1824. Giovannino Guareschi also lived in Le Roncole and his Mondo Piccolo was set there.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Rocca_Pallavicino.jpg/250px-Rocca_Pallavicino.jpg
